Commentary Text: Chahal to Ashwin, out Stumped!! Has Ashwin been stumped? de Kock certainly seems confident. It's a fair delivery, the bat is in the air, Ashwin is way short as well and he's OUT. Commentary Text: Kulwant Khejroliya to Axar, out Lbw!! Axar has been given OUT LBW and he wants a review. This looked adjacent to the naked eye. It's a fair delivery and there's no bat as well. The impact seems to be in front of middle, the height isn't an issue. No edge, says Ultraedge. Hawk-Eye in, three reds and Axar is OUT. Simple call for umpire Ravi and Khejroliya has struck with his last ball. This was full and came back with the angle, Axar shuffled a long way across on the flick, once he missed, it was curtains, decided to take a chance as he reviewed, but to no avail. Axar lbw b Kulwant Khejroliya 2(3)

Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Stoinis, leg byes, 1 run, loud shout for LBW and RCB want a review. Kohli looked very keen to challenge the call. It's a fair delivery from Sundar, it has pitched in line, but is it spinning down leg? There's no bat and Ultraedge confirms it. I don't think it straightened enough, Hawk-Eye in and it's missing the leg-stump. RCB have lost their review. This was tossed up on middle and was spinning into the right-hander, Stoinis swept and missed, was struck on the pads, in front of leg and the angle was traking it down the leg-stump. The ball rolls away towards the off-side, the fielder has a shy at the bowler's end and concedes an overthrow

Commentary Text: Mujeeb to Kohli, out Bowled!! What a dream ball! Absolute ripper! Take a bow, young Mujeeb! He has gone through the gate with a traditional googly that's spun back in a mile. And it's the legendary Virat Kohli that he has dismissed. Hold your breath and take a moment out to applaud this young man. What an effort! Nothing really that Kohli did wrong here, got a stride forward for the drive and maybe, we can say he was a touch loose on the stroke but who could have accounted for this turn? Massive wicket! The game is wide open now I would say. We all know how big Kohli is in run chases. Kohli b Mujeeb 21(16) [4s-4]

Commentary Text: Axar to Brendon McCullum, out Caught by Mujeeb!! Golden duck for McCullum! Huge blow and aren't the KXIP boys pumped! This is a massive strike and they know it. Full marks to Ashwin, bold move to start with Axar and it's paid off. Slowed up nicely and dragged outside off, McCullum was making room to go aerial on the off-side but only managed a slice. Straight to Mujeeb who gobbled it up at point. The hosts have been jolted early. Brendon McCullum c Mujeeb b Axar 0(1)
